        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 30 at 6:48PM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 647 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated strong thunderstorms along a
line extending from 2 miles southwest of Wardville to 7 miles
southeast of Big Cedar. Movement was south at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Octavia...                        Clayton Lake State Park...
Sardis...                         Pittsburg...
Kiowa...                          Tuskahoma...
Yanush...                         Clayton...
Big Cedar...                      Stanley...
Nashoba...                        Kiamichi...
Whitesboro...                     Albion...
Blanco...                         Talihina...
Muse...                           Honobia...
Ashland...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
